Association - relationship where each object has its own life cycle. Teacher Student example. A teacher can have multiple students and student can have multiple teachers. Both can create and delete independently, no ownership.
Aggregation - There is ownership and a child can have a owner. Department and teacher example. "has-a" relationship
Composition - strong aggregation and strong ownership. Child cannot exist without parent. house and rooms example. rooms cannot exist without house.
is-a relation is inheritance
has-a relation is aggregation or composition. 